i-whbv/09-biz-meta-ai-whbv-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600-v2.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Eric Helgas for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>The paid product opens up a new revenue stream for Meta, which is planning to spend tens of billions of dollars on artificial intelligence this year.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Apple Sues OpenAI, Accusing It of Stealing Company Secrets</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/10/technology/apple-openai-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/10/technology/apple-openai-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/10/technology/apple-openai-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The two companies struck a deal in 2024 to offer A.I. services on Apple devices, but their partnership has soured.</description><dc:creator>Kalley Huang and Cade Metz</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 21:08:14 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Intellectual property</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Corporate espionage</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/10/multimedia/10biz-apple-openai2-tlmg/10biz-apple-openai2-tlmg-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Karsten Moran for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Apple made several accusations against OpenAI in its lawsuit, including that OpenAI had asked job candidates from Apple to share details about secret projects.</media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>